Arab Funds to Give $200m in Loans for Syria Power Projects

-- B y   L i n a   I b r a h i m   a n d   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 
2011-04-03T07:36:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/arab-funds-to-give-200m-in-loans-for-syria-power-projects.html
The Arab Fund for Economic and
Social Development and the Saudi Fund for Development will
give loans worth more than $200 million to finance a power
project in  Syria , the Syrian  finance ministry  said.  The ministry will sign an agreement for a loan of 30
million Kuwaiti dinars ($108 million) with the Kuwait-based
AFESD and another 375 million Saudi riyals ($100 million)
agreement with the Saudi fund this week, it said on its
 website  today.  The loans, due to fund a power generation project in
the eastern province of Deir Ez-Zor, will be signed during
meetings of Arab finance ministers in Damascus on April 6-
7, it said.  A coordination meeting will also be held with six Arab
funds, namely AFESD, the SFD, the  Islamic Development Bank ,
the Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development, the Abu
Dhabi Fund for Development and the OPEC Fund to discuss the
financing of a project that aims to channel water from the
Tigris River to the northeastern governorate of Hassakeh,
it said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
